## Pull Request Guidelines

### Change Traceability Requirements

All changes must be digitally traceable. When creating PRs, ensure:

**For Stakeholder-Initiated Changes:**

- Link to Jira ticket in PR description
- Changes affect customer-perceived functionality
- Backed by company strategy

**For Team/Developer-Initiated Changes:**

- Use appropriate GitHub tags:
  - `Lights On`: System maintenance
  - `Technical Debt`: Cleanup, refactoring
  - `Technical Design`: Architecture improvements

**PR Description Checklist:**

- [ ] Include ticket link (if applicable) or select appropriate tag
- [ ] Briefly explain change motivation
- [ ] Ensure all changes are digitally traceable
- [ ] Apply appropriate GitHub label using: `gh pr edit <PR_NUMBER> --add-label "<LABEL_NAME>"`
- [ ] If unsure about categorization, consult team via Slack

### Applying Labels to PRs

After creating a PR, apply the appropriate label using the GitHub CLI:

```bash
# For system maintenance (CI/CD, build scripts, deployment configs)
gh pr edit <PR_NUMBER> --add-label "Lights On"

# For cleanup and refactoring (code improvements, dependency updates)
gh pr edit <PR_NUMBER> --add-label "Technical Debt"

# For architecture improvements (design patterns, new frameworks)
gh pr edit <PR_NUMBER> --add-label "Technical Design"
```

**Label Classification Guidelines:**

- **Lights On**: CI/CD workflows, build configurations, deployment scripts, monitoring setup
- **Technical Debt**: Code refactoring, dependency updates, performance improvements, test improvements
- **Technical Design**: New architectural patterns, framework additions, major design changes
